      <scopecontent id="aspace_212e4c7c660223a296b249ed01cca623">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This small collection contains items relating to Charles Winslow Burpee and to Yale College. Included are two undated letters to Burpee from friends and five communications concerning Skull and Bones. There is also a photograph of Skull and Bones members dating around 1883 and two impressions of the Skull and Bones seal. The remainder of the collection consists of Yale memorabilia such as programs, football tickets, Yale pins and other souvenir objects.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_ea61db0efd3b4bf2dfa2f28590e13e42">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Arranged by record type.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <bioghist id="aspace_5a2f93ece884bcdbe743cddd0049a733">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Charles W. Burpee: Yale, B.A., 1883; editor of <title render="italic">
               <part>Waterbury American</part>
            </title> (Ct.), 1883-1891; of <title render="italic">
               <part>Bridgeport Standard</part>
            </title> (Ct.), 1891-1895; of <title render="italic">
               <part>Hartford Courant</part>
            </title>, 1895-1904; with Phoenix Mutual Life Insurance Company 1904-1935; literary editor, <title render="italic">
               <part>Hartford Times</part>
            </title>, 1930-1935; author of books on Connecticut history.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <userestrict id="aspace_7b3a0dc627d4095bff87634444351b33">
